  "body": "\nGO:0045022  early endosome to late endosome transport\nDefinition (GO:0045022 GONUTS page)\nThe directed movement of substances, in membrane-bounded vesicles, from the early sorting endosomes to the late sorting endosomes; transport occurs along microtubules and can be experimentally blocked with microtubule-depolymerizing drugs. PMID:29980602\n\nNot always microtubule dependent (in fission yeast it's actin dependent)\n remove gloss:\ntransport occurs along microtubules and can be experimentally blocked with microtubule-depolymerizing drugs\n\n\n",
